            <title><![CDATA[DevSecOps Explained for Beginners]]></title>
            <link>https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps</link>
            <guid>https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps</guid>
            <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 16:38:53 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Learn DevSecOps from basics to lifecycle with real examples.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<blockquote>
<p>🚀 A simple guide to understanding DevSecOps and why it matters</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-slide-version-canva">🎨 Slide Version (Canva)<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-slide-version-canva" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🎨 Slide Version (Canva)" title="Direct link to 🎨 Slide Version (Canva)" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>👉 View full presentation here:<br>
<!-- -->🔗 <a href="https://www.canva.com/design/DAG_uCMdKUU/sgVgyobe71QhR5-EtSNutg/edit?utm_content=DAG_uCMdKUU&amp;utm_campaign=designshare&amp;utm_medium=link2&amp;utm_source=sharebutton" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">https://www.canva.com/design/DAG_uCMdKUU/sgVgyobe71QhR5-EtSNutg/edit?utm_content=DAG_uCMdKUU&amp;utm_campaign=designshare&amp;utm_medium=link2&amp;utm_source=sharebutton</a></p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-what-is-devsecops">🧩 What is DevSecOps?<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-what-is-devsecops" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🧩 What is DevSecOps?" title="Direct link to 🧩 What is DevSecOps?" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>DevSecOps stands for:</p>
<p>👉 <strong>Dev + Sec + Ops</strong></p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>Dev (Development):</strong> Writing code</li>
<li class=""><strong>Sec (Security):</strong> Protecting systems</li>
<li class=""><strong>Ops (Operations):</strong> Running and maintaining infrastructure</li>
</ul>
<p>💡 The key idea:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>All teams work <strong>together, continuously, and automatically</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-devsecops-lifecycle">🔄 DevSecOps Lifecycle<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-devsecops-lifecycle" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔄 DevSecOps Lifecycle" title="Direct link to 🔄 DevSecOps Lifecycle" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>A typical DevSecOps workflow includes:</p>
<ol>
<li class="">Collaboration &amp; Communication</li>
<li class="">Threat Modeling</li>
<li class="">QA Integration</li>
<li class="">Security Checks &amp; Scans</li>
<li class="">Vulnerability Management</li>
<li class="">CI/CD</li>
<li class="">Infrastructure as Code (IaC)</li>
<li class="">Container Security</li>
<li class="">Key Management</li>
<li class="">Continuous Monitoring</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-1-collaboration--communication">🤝 1. Collaboration &amp; Communication<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-1-collaboration--communication" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🤝 1. Collaboration &amp; Communication" title="Direct link to 🤝 1. Collaboration &amp; Communication" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="why-it-matters">Why it matters<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#why-it-matters" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Why it matters" title="Direct link to Why it matters" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>Teams (Dev – Sec – Ops) should:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Work together</li>
<li class="">Share information continuously</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="benefits">Benefits<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#benefits" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Benefits" title="Direct link to Benefits" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">🔥 Early bug detection</li>
<li class="">🔥 Fewer conflicts</li>
<li class="">🔥 Faster development</li>
<li class="">🔥 Stronger security</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-2-threat-modeling">🧠 2. Threat Modeling<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-2-threat-modeling" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🧠 2. Threat Modeling" title="Direct link to 🧠 2. Threat Modeling" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="what-is-it">What is it?<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#what-is-it" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What is it?" title="Direct link to What is it?" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<p>Thinking like a hacker before building the system:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“If I were an attacker, where would I attack?”</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="key-questions">Key questions:<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#key-questions" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Key questions:" title="Direct link to Key questions:" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">What does the system include?</li>
<li class="">What are the critical assets?</li>
<li class="">What threats exist?</li>
<li class="">How can we prevent them?</li>
</ul>
<p>💡 Fixing issues early = cheaper and easier</p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-3-qa-integration">🧪 3. QA Integration<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-3-qa-integration" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🧪 3. QA Integration" title="Direct link to 🧪 3. QA Integration" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="traditional-approach-">Traditional approach ❌<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#traditional-approach-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Traditional approach ❌" title="Direct link to Traditional approach ❌" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ol>
<li class="">Code</li>
<li class="">Deploy</li>
<li class="">Test at the end</li>
</ol>
<p>👉 Result:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Many bugs</li>
<li class="">Delays</li>
<li class="">Stress</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="devsecops-approach-">DevSecOps approach ✅<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#devsecops-approach-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to DevSecOps approach ✅" title="Direct link to DevSecOps approach ✅" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Test continuously</li>
<li class="">Automate testing</li>
</ul>
<p>👉 Result:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Bugs found early</li>
<li class="">Faster releases</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-4-security-checks--scans">🔍 4. Security Checks &amp; Scans<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-4-security-checks--scans" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔍 4. Security Checks &amp; Scans" title="Direct link to 🔍 4. Security Checks &amp; Scans" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="sast">SAST<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#sast" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to SAST" title="Direct link to SAST" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Scan source code</li>
<li class="">Find vulnerabilities before running</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="dast">DAST<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#dast" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to DAST" title="Direct link to DAST" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Test running applications</li>
<li class="">Simulate real-world attacks</li>
</ul>
<p>🎯 Goal:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Detect vulnerabilities as early as possible</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="️-5-vulnerability-management">🛡️ 5. Vulnerability Management<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#%EF%B8%8F-5-vulnerability-management" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🛡️ 5. Vulnerability Management" title="Direct link to 🛡️ 5. Vulnerability Management" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Security is not just about finding bugs — it's about managing them.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="process">Process:<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#process" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Process:" title="Direct link to Process:" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ol>
<li class="">Scan</li>
<li class="">Assess severity</li>
<li class="">Prioritize</li>
<li class="">Fix continuously</li>
</ol>
<p>👉 Focus on critical issues first</p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="️-6-cicd">⚙️ 6. CI/CD<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#%EF%B8%8F-6-cicd" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ⚙️ 6. CI/CD" title="Direct link to ⚙️ 6. CI/CD" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>CI/CD automates the development pipeline:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">✅ Build automatically</li>
<li class="">✅ Test automatically</li>
<li class="">✅ Deploy automatically</li>
<li class="">✅ Integrate security checks</li>
</ul>
<p>💡 Every code push triggers automation</p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="️-7-infrastructure-as-code-iac">🏗️ 7. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#%EF%B8%8F-7-infrastructure-as-code-iac" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🏗️ 7. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)" title="Direct link to 🏗️ 7. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Infrastructure is defined using code.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="benefits-1">Benefits:<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#benefits-1" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Benefits:" title="Direct link to Benefits:" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Easy to manage</li>
<li class="">Consistent environments</li>
<li class="">Reduced human error</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-why-devsecops">⚡ Why DevSecOps?<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-why-devsecops" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ⚡ Why DevSecOps?" title="Direct link to ⚡ Why DevSecOps?" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="old-way-">Old way ❌<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#old-way-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Old way ❌" title="Direct link to Old way ❌" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Teams work separately</li>
<li class="">Security comes late</li>
</ul>
<p>👉 Result:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Late bug detection</li>
<li class="">Expensive fixes</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="devsecops-way-">DevSecOps way ✅<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#devsecops-way-" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to DevSecOps way ✅" title="Direct link to DevSecOps way ✅" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Teams collaborate</li>
<li class="">Security is built-in</li>
</ul>
<p>👉 Result:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Faster delivery</li>
<li class="">Better security</li>
<li class="">Higher efficiency</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-final-thoughts">🧠 Final Thoughts<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-final-thoughts" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🧠 Final Thoughts" title="Direct link to 🧠 Final Thoughts" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>DevSecOps is not just a process —<br>
<!-- -->👉 it is a <strong>mindset</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Build fast, but secure from the beginning.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-summary">📌 Summary<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/DevSecOps#-summary" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 📌 Summary" title="Direct link to 📌 Summary" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li class="">DevSecOps = Dev + Sec + Ops</li>
<li class="">Focus on <strong>automation + collaboration + security early</strong></li>
<li class="">Essential skill for modern developers</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>🔥 Start your DevSecOps journey today!</p>]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Blockchain & Web3 – Guide from Basics to Practice]]></title>
            <link>https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3</link>
            <guid>https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3</guid>
            <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 16:38:53 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Explaining Blockchain, Web3, Smart Contracts, and Web3 Wallets in an Easy-to-Understand Way for Beginners]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-introduction">📌 Introduction<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-introduction" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 📌 Introduction" title="Direct link to 📌 Introduction" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Blockchain and Web3 are core technologies of the new generation of the Internet.<br>
<!-- -->If Web2 helps users <strong>interact and create content</strong>, then Web3 aims for a bigger goal:<br>
<!-- -->👉 <strong>giving users ownership of data and digital assets</strong>.</p>
<p>This article is designed for <strong>beginners</strong>, helping you:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Understand what Blockchain is</li>
<li class="">Understand how Web3 differs from Web2</li>
<li class="">Know how Smart Contracts work</li>
<li class="">Get an overview before diving deeper</li>
</ul>
<p>📊 <strong>Illustrative slide for the entire lesson:</strong><br>
<!-- -->👉 <a href="https://www.canva.com/design/DAHAWicpH1w/pfiXZRFKgXGG2dhy8E4q_g/edit?utm_content=DAHAWicpH1w&amp;utm_campaign=designshare&amp;utm_medium=link2&amp;utm_source=sharebutton" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">Blockchain &amp; Web3 – Canva</a></p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="1️⃣-what-is-blockchain">1️⃣ What is Blockchain?<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#1%EF%B8%8F%E2%83%A3-what-is-blockchain" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 1️⃣ What is Blockchain?" title="Direct link to 1️⃣ What is Blockchain?" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Blockchain (blockchain) is a <strong>distributed database</strong>, where data is:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Recorded into <strong>Blocks</strong></li>
<li class="">Blocks are <strong>linked together through encryption</strong></li>
<li class="">Data that has been recorded cannot be modified</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-key-features-of-blockchain">🔗 Key Features of Blockchain<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-key-features-of-blockchain" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔗 Key Features of Blockchain" title="Direct link to 🔗 Key Features of Blockchain" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>Decentralized</strong>: No central server</li>
<li class=""><strong>Transparent</strong>: Anyone can verify transactions</li>
<li class=""><strong>Immutable</strong>: Recorded data is almost impossible to delete</li>
</ul>
<p>📌 Example:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>When you transfer money on the blockchain, that transaction will be recorded permanently and everyone can check it.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="2️⃣-basic-structure-of-blockchain--web3">2️⃣ Basic Structure of Blockchain &amp; Web3<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#2%EF%B8%8F%E2%83%A3-basic-structure-of-blockchain--web3" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 2️⃣ Basic Structure of Blockchain &amp; Web3" title="Direct link to 2️⃣ Basic Structure of Blockchain &amp; Web3" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>A Web3 ecosystem usually consists of the following components:</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-block">🔹 Block<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-block" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔹 Block" title="Direct link to 🔹 Block" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Contains transaction data</li>
<li class="">Has a hash of the previous block</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-hash">🔹 Hash<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-hash" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔹 Hash" title="Direct link to 🔹 Hash" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Is an encrypted string representing the data</li>
<li class="">Changing just 1 character → hash changes completely</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-node">🔹 Node<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-node" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔹 Node" title="Direct link to 🔹 Node" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Computers participating in the blockchain network</li>
<li class="">Each node stores a copy of the data</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-wallet-web3-wallet">🔹 Wallet (Web3 Wallet)<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-wallet-web3-wallet" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔹 Wallet (Web3 Wallet)" title="Direct link to 🔹 Wallet (Web3 Wallet)" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Represents the <strong>digital identity</strong> of the user</li>
<li class="">Stores private key</li>
<li class="">Examples: MetaMask, Trust Wallet</li>
</ul>
<p>📊 <strong>Illustrative slide for the structure section:</strong><br>
<!-- -->👉 <a href="https://www.canva.com/design/DAHAWicpH1w/pfiXZRFKgXGG2dhy8E4q_g/edit?utm_content=DAHAWicpH1w&amp;utm_campaign=designshare&amp;utm_medium=link2&amp;utm_source=sharebutton" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">View on Canva</a></p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="3️⃣-what-is-a-smart-contract">3️⃣ What is a Smart Contract?<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#3%EF%B8%8F%E2%83%A3-what-is-a-smart-contract" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 3️⃣ What is a Smart Contract?" title="Direct link to 3️⃣ What is a Smart Contract?" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>A Smart Contract is:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>A program that runs automatically on the blockchain</strong>, without intermediaries.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="-features">🧠 Features<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#-features" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🧠 Features" title="Direct link to 🧠 Features" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<ul>
<li class="">Automatically executes</li>
<li class="">Cannot be edited after deployment</li>
<li class="">Public &amp; transparent</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="️-simple-smart-contract-example-solidity">✍️ Simple Smart Contract Example (Solidity)<a href="https://tienthanh23072007-stack.github.io/my-doku/blog/blockchain-web3#%EF%B8%8F-simple-smart-contract-example-solidity" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ✍️ Simple Smart Contract Example (Solidity)" title="Direct link to ✍️ Simple Smart Contract Example (Solidity)" translate="no">​</a></h3>
<div class="language-solidity codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-solidity codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">pragma solidity ^0.8.0;</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">contract HelloWeb3 {</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    function hello() public pure returns(string memory) {</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">        return "Hello Web3!";</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">    }</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">}</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
